<p> <note type="source" target="#right(351)">Ysv<hi rend="sup">PT</hi>: eteṣāñ ca tathā pañcaguṇasthānaṃ śṛṇu priye | asthi māṃsaṃ loma nāḍī tvak ceti pṛthivīguṇāḥ |</note><anchor xml:id="351"/><note type="testium" target="#right(352)">SSP 1.37: asthimāṃsatvaṅnāḍīromāṇīti pañcaguṇā bhūmiḥ |</note><anchor xml:id="352"/><app><lem wit="#E #N1 #N2">tatra</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#B #E #L #N1 #N2 #U2">pṛthvīyā</lem><rdg wit="#P">pṛthivyāḥ</rdg><rdg wit="#ceteri">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#E #N1 #N2 #U2">guṇāḥ</lem><rdg wit="#L #P">paṃcaguṇāḥ kathyaṃte</rdg><rdg wit="#B">paṃcaguṇāḥ | athyate |</rdg><rdg wit="#ceteri">om.</rdg></app>/ <app><lem wit="#B #E #L #P #N1 #N2">asthi</lem><rdg wit="#U2">asti</rdg><rdg wit="#ceteri">om.</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#P">māṃsaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">māṃsa</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">om.</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#E #P #N1 #N2 #U2">lomāni</lem><rdg wit="#B #L">tvak</rdg><rdg wit="#ceteri">om.</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#N1 #N2">tvak</lem><rdg wit="#U2">tvakḥ</rdg><rdg wit="#E">vāk</rdg><rdg wit="#P">vākṛt</rdg><rdg wit="#ceteri">om.</rdg></app>// <note type="source" target="#right(353)">Ysv<hi rend="sup">PT</hi>: kṣudhātṛṣṇālasyanidrā glāniś ca pañca vāriṇaḥ | rogo lajjā bhayodvegau dhāraṇā ca marud guṇāḥ |</note><anchor xml:id="353"/><note type="testium" target="#right(354)">SSP 1.38: lālā mūtraṃ śukraṃ śoṇitaṃ sveda iti pañcaguṇā āpaḥ |</note><anchor xml:id="354"/><app><lem wit="#ceteri">tatrodakaguṇāḥ</lem><rdg wit="#N1">netrodake guṇāḥ</rdg><rdg wit="#N2">netrodakaguṇāḥ</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">lālā</lem><rdg wit="#B #L">lāla°</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#E #N2 #U2">mūtraṃ</lem><rdg wit="#N1 #U1">mutraṃ</rdg><rdg wit="#B #L">°mutra°</rdg><rdg wit="#P">°muvaṃ</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#ceteri">śukraṃ</lem><rdg wit="#E">śuklaṃ</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">raktaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#N2">om.</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#ceteri">prasvedaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#U1">svedaḥ</rdg></app>// <note type="testium" target="#right(355)">SSP 1.39: kṣudhā tṛṣā nidrā kāntir ālasyam iti pañcaguṇaṃ tejaḥ |</note><anchor xml:id="355"/>tejaso <app><lem wit="#ceteri">guṇāḥ</lem><rdg wit="#U2">guṇaḥ</rdg></app>/ <app><lem wit="#ceteri">kṣudhā</lem><rdg wit="#B">kṣudhāṃ</rdg></app>// tṛṣā// nidrā// <app><lem wit="#E #P">glāniḥ</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">glāni</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#ceteri">ālasyaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#U1">ālasya</rdg></app>// <note type="testium" target="#right(356)">SSP 1.40: dhāvanaṃ plavanaṃ prasāraṇaṃ ākuñcanaṃ nirodhanam iti pañcaguṇo vayuḥ |</note><anchor xml:id="356"/><app><lem wit="#ceteri">vāyor gu</lem><rdg wit="#B #N2 #U2">vāyo</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">vāyu</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">ṇāḥ</lem><rdg wit="#U1">guṇā</rdg></app>/ dhāvanaṃ// <app><lem wit="#ceteri">majjanaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#N2">majana</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">mano°</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#ceteri">nirodhanaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#U1">°rodhanaṃ</rdg><rdg wit="#N2">virodhana</rdg></app>// prasāraṇam// <app><lem wit="#ceteri">ākuñcanaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#N2">ākūrcana</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">ceti</lem><rdg wit="#U2">om.</rdg></app>// <note type="testium" target="#right(357)">SSP 1.41: rāgo dveṣo bhayaṃ lajjā moha iti pañcaguṇa ākaśaḥ |</note><anchor xml:id="357"/>ākāśasya <app><lem wit="#ceteri">guṇāḥ</lem><rdg wit="#U1">guṇaḥ</rdg></app>/ <app><lem wit="#U2">rāgaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">rāga</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#P #U2">dveṣaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#N1">°dveṣo</rdg><rdg wit="#E">°dveṣau</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">dveṣau</rdg><rdg wit="#B #L">dveṣ°</rdg></app>// bhayaṃ// lajjā// <app><lem wit="#E #P #N1 #U2">mohaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#B #L #N2">moha</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">mohā</rdg></app>// <note type="source" target="#right(358)">Ysv<hi rend="sup">PT</hi>: etaj jñānenaiva teṣāṃ buddhir utpadyate śubhā | yadyapi sargakāṇḍe pṛthvyāder guṇā uktās tathāpy etaj jñānenety anena kāryakāraṇabhāvadarśanāya punar ucyante |</note><anchor xml:id="358"/>tad <app><lem wit="#E #P #U2">anantaram e</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">anaṃtaraṃ</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#U2 #P">tādṛśy e</lem><rdg wit="#N2">etādṛśī</rdg><rdg wit="#N1">etādṛśā</rdg><rdg wit="#L #U1">etādaśī</rdg><rdg wit="#E">ekādaśī</rdg><rdg wit="#B">metādaśī</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">kā</lem><rdg wit="#E">kā</rdg><rdg wit="#B #L">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">buddhir u</lem><rdg wit="#P">buddher</rdg></app>tpadyate/ <note type="source" target="#right(359)">Ysv<hi rend="sup">PT</hi>: mano buddhir ahaṅkāraś cittaṃ caitanyameva ca | ete pañcaprakārāś ca antaḥkaraṇasambhavāḥ |</note><anchor xml:id="359"/><note type="testium" target="#right(360)">SSP 1.42: mano buddhir ahaṅkāraś cittaṃ caitanyam ity antaḥkaraṇapañcakam |</note><anchor xml:id="360"/>mano <app><lem wit="#ceteri">buddhir a</lem><rdg wit="#E">buddhy</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#B #L #U1">haṃkāraś ci</lem><rdg wit="#E">ahaṃkārāś</rdg><rdg wit="#U2">ahaṃkāraḥ ||</rdg><rdg wit="#B">ahaṃkāra | ś</rdg><rdg wit="#N1 #N2">ahaṃkāra</rdg></app>ttaṃ <app><lem wit="#B #E #L #P #U2">caitanyaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">om.</rdg></app> ceti/ ete <app><lem wit="#E">pañcaprakārā</lem><rdg wit="#N2">paṃcāprakārā</rdg><rdg wit="#U2">paṃcaprakāraḥ</rdg><rdg wit="#P">paṃcāpiprakārā</rdg><rdg wit="#B">paṃcāpiprakāra |</rdg><rdg wit="#L">paṃcāpiprakārāḥ</rdg><rdg wit="#N1 #U1">paṃcāpiprakārā</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">aṃtaḥkaraṇasya</lem><rdg wit="#N2">aṃtakaraṇasya</rdg><rdg wit="#B #L">aṃtaḥkarṇsya</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">aṃtaḥkarṇva</rdg></app>/ <note type="source" target="#right(361)">SSP 1.43: saṃkalpo vikalpo mūrcchā jaḍatā mananam iti pañcaguṇaṃ manaḥ</note><anchor xml:id="361"/>manaṣaḥ <app><lem wit="#ceteri">pañcaguṇāḥ</lem><rdg wit="#E">ye ca guṇāḥ</rdg></app>/ <app><lem wit="#N2">saṃkalpaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#L">sakalpa</rdg><rdg wit="#ceteri">saṃkalpa</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#N1">vikalpaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">vikalpa</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#N2">mūrkhatvaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#N1 #U1">mūrṣatvaṃ</rdg><rdg wit="#E">mūrkhatvā</rdg><rdg wit="#ceteri">mūrkhatva</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">jaḍatā</lem><rdg wit="#E">lasatā</rdg></app>// mananaṃ <app><lem wit="#ceteri">ceti</lem><rdg wit="#U1">ceti vā</rdg><rdg wit="#N1">ceti ete paṃcāpiprakārā aṃtaḥkaraṇasya ma</rdg></app>/ <note type="source" target="#right(362)">SSP 1.44: viveko vairāgyaṃ śāntiḥ santoṣaḥ kṣameti pañcaguṇā buddhiḥ |</note><anchor xml:id="362"/><note type="source" target="#right(363)">Ysv<hi rend="sup">PT</hi>: mananāmananaṃ jñeyaṃ buddhyādipañca pañca tu | vivekaśāntisantoṣakṣamāvairāgyateti ca | ete pañcaguṇā buddher ahaṅkāraguṇān śṛṇu |</note><anchor xml:id="363"/><app><lem wit="#E #L #P #N1">buddheḥ</lem><rdg wit="#B">buddhe</rdg><rdg wit="#ceteri">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#B #E #L #P #N1">pañcaguṇāḥ</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">om.</rdg></app>/ <app><lem wit="#P #N1 #N2">vivekaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#E #U2">viveko</rdg><rdg wit="#B #L #U1">viveka</rdg></app>// <app><lem wit="#E #U2">vairāgyaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">vairāgya</rdg></app>// śāntiḥ// <app><lem wit="#ceteri">santoṣaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#N2">santoṣa</rdg><rdg wit="#U2">santoṣāḥ</rdg></app>// kṣamā <app><lem wit="#ceteri">ceti</lem><rdg wit="#U1">vā</rdg></app>// <note type="philcomm" target="#right(362)">Witness D resumes its evidence from here.</note><anchor xml:id="362"/></p>
